here is changing from a downflow to an upflow. During the appearance of\nflashed Ca II 8542 \\AA\\ cores, the atmosphere is upflowing most of the time,\nand only 38\\% of the flashed profiles are associated with downflows. We find a\nscenario that remarkably explains the recent empirical findings of downflowing\numbral flashes as a natural consequence of the presence of standing\noscillations above sunspot umbrae.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Jan 2021 21:00:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-27"}
